\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Diary 15
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Monday
\par The Boss is back this morning as per usual, no thanks for holding the fort for the
 week-end. Just a swearing because I didn't fill in the running book yesterday.  I think he was just tired because there was only 1 wagon out.  He said if anything happened nobody else would know what was going out.  I told him if anything happened I was 
t
he one on call and nobody else would bother their backside so what difference did it make. That just made it worse so I just shut up and went outside for ten minutes.  When I went back in I just got on with my DLY notes off the Tippers and he was alright 
after that.
\par 
\par Tuesday 
\par Things were a bit better today. }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 told me the new Portakabin in the yard was for us because the company had expanded in so many different areas, office space was getting scarce.  Because the livestock is a department that is individual
 from the rest we are the only ones that can really move out. I don't think it will work but time will tell.
\par We lifted the \tab Portakabin into place this afternoon.  It looks like we will be moving in sooner than I thought we would.
\par 
\par Weds
\par We found out today t
hat DEFRA are going to allow live sales of store sheep in the markets.  That was good news until we found out that all sales of sheep store or fat would be classed as store sales and the livestock would have to be licensed into the market and out again.  
I
 can see the point in licensing store sheep because they are coming off one farm going through a market then probably onto another farm so that they can trace their movement.  I can't understand why they want to license fat sheep because once they leave t
he market they go directly to the abattoir where they have to be killed within 48 hours.  I can't see the point of license when the animals are going to get killed, they won't spread any disease then.
\par 
\par Thursday Early start again this morning, sheep to lead 
into Longtown.  I don't mind working but I am supposed to be a Transport manager. How I am supposed to keep up with what's going on and where the wagon and drivers are when I'm getting sent out all the time.  The way livestock haulage is drivers don't wan
t
 to do the job now, they don't want  the dirt and hassle.  Drivers now can drive a curtain sider, be parked up at  a decent time of night and keep clean and get paid as much so it's no wonder nobody wants to drive a livestock wagon.  One of the biggest th
i
ngs is the rules and regulations involved in livestock transport.  Because of the way things are in road haulage everybody is short of drivers so that is one of the reasons I have to drive as much as I do.  The only thing is I'm driving more and more and 
I
'm getting a bit sick of it. I like driving but I'm supposed to be a manager not a driver. If I wanted to be a driver all my life I wouldn't have accepted a job in the office.  The other thing with me being on a salary I don't get extra for starting early
 or working week-ends and it's happening more and more. I'm getting to the stage of getting out and doing something else.
\par 
\par Fri
\par Me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 were thinking about selling the house we have got and moving. We have been thinking of it for a while and then we thought if we sell the house we have got we might be able to build a house on the island where }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281 's parents are.  We mentioned this to }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
's Mam and Dad and they said why not build on their croft. If they gave us a piece of ground we just have to build the house.  This sounded good to me, it could just be the change I need.  We sent away for prices of kit houses to see how much it would 
cost and whether we could afford it or not.  Fingers crossed we will be able to afford to do it.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid484382 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Sat
\par Some of the brochures arrived this morning and at a first glance it looks as if we will be able to build a house.  The only thing is it depends on now is
 how much our own house is worth.  We have decided to pant our house and tidy it up and get it valued to give us an idea of how much it is worth. We have also decided to look into building a house on Islay properly to see what it will entail.
