t a lot of sheep in Cumbria yet, local markets are having to canvas further away to keep numbers up in their sales. After this week it shouldn't be as bad because of the abattoirs not wanting hoggs.
\par I couldn't understand why when we are as quiet as we are I had to go for the sheep this morning as we have plenty of drivers. The only thing I could think of is because I am on a salary it wasn't costing them wages
 for me, to go for them. It would be a waste of time saying anything because my boss would just make up an excuse.  All this is just making it easier for me to make the decision to build a house on Islay.
\par 
\par Fri
\par Tensions are running a bit high at work becaus
e of diversification and wages. Because the company has grown by at least a third in the year, more wagons, more staff but no more room.  The mechanics haven't got enough room in the garage, we haven't got enough room in the office, the warehouse isn't bi
g enough, the yard is too small and the wages are the same way.  The wage offer this year was an insult. It's alright expanding but if you don't keep the staff up to date as well you are wasting your time. As a result, tensions are high.
\par I fell out with one of the mechanics today over one of the vans because he wanted to wash their van and use one of the others. It was a bit petty really, it was just because of the way things are.
\par 
\par Sat
\par I started cleaning the yard and doing some repairs today.  I didn't get much done in the morning because }{\fs24\insrsid484382 [friends were]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 in to see us so I didn't get a lot done.  I got on better this afternoon, It was quite good. I could work at my own pace not telephones and no hassle. There is quite a bit to do because I got nothing done last
 year because things were so busy. I want to get everything painted and tidies up so I can get everything valued to see what it will cost to build or if it is feasible.
\par 
\par Sun
\par Me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and a few of the lads from work went for a game of golf this morning.
  We went to Langholm where the golf course is up the hill overlooking the town.  The view off the top is really nice and I enjoyed my game.  I haven't played for over a year and played quite well which made it good.   
\par 
