\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Things seem to be getting  worse with DEFRA, we don\rquote t know whether we are doing right or wrong with us being as near th
e Border we are working under two sets of rules.  On the Scottish side you have SEERAD and on the English side DEFRA.  In Scotland you can just about do anything but in England it\rquote 
s just a nightmare.  They fetch new rules out nearly every day.  In Scotland you can pick up and deliver livestock from markets and farms and deliver them wherever and as many deliveries as you like.  In England you can\rquote 
t mix fat stock and store stock on the same vehicle.  You can pick up a max of 5 farms and deliver to 1 farm or 
1 abattoir or you can pick up 1 farm or market and deliver to 5 abattoirs but only 1 farm unless the farms have a multiple pick up and drop off licence in which case you can deliver a max of 5 farms and that\rquote s just the basis.
