\par Out on a wagon today,
 one of the drivers phoned in ill this morning so took his load away into Stirling with a load of cattle then into Stirling market for a load of sheep.  It was good to get out of the office and away from the phones to see a lot of faces I hadn\rquote 
t seen for a long time.  Pre F&M I used to go with the van every week.  At that time I could get in the region of 3 to 4 thousand sheep.  Today I got 400, big change but it was good to see everybody again and catch up on what\rquote s been happening.

