\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Thursday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 I was loading stock into Longtown this morning, the marke
t was busy.  There were wagons and land rovers and trailer queued on the road for about 100 yds either side of the market entrance.  Because of DEFRA rules where the land rovers used to empty is classed as a public entrance and car park, so all the land r
o
vers have to come in and empty in the same place as the wagons.  Once they are empty the driver could walk all over the market then out of the public entrance back into the market into his land rover without washing his trailer out and drive to Cornwall i
f he wanted as long as he washed out when he got there.  So in that case why they can\rquote t empty where they normally do \endash  there will be an accident shortly with all the vehicles mounting up.  They have no common sense at all, DEFRA.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Friday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 I was hoping to get finished early today.  Me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  are going to Huntly above Aberdeen tomorrow for }{\fs24\insrsid11670163 [friend}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s}{
\fs24\insrsid11670163  dad\rquote s]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  funeral.  I spent most of the day on the phone to the Dutchman and the Irishman.  The cattle are now coming a week on Monday.  The Dutch man is going to 
collect the cattle in Denmark next Sunday, take them to Holland, rest them for 24 hours then fetch them over.
\par 
\par Me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  left about 8pm, we are going to Stirling tonight to stop with friends at Stirling then head for Huntley in the morning.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Sat
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 We lef
t at 6,30 this morning and picked 2 of our friends up on the way out of Stirling.  We got there about 10am.  There was a lot of people at the funeral, about 4 to 5 hundred.  We went to a bowling club where his father was Vice President after the funeral. 
 Willie is taking it pretty bad. Both him and Chrissie looked as if they both needed a good night\rquote 
s sleep.  We left there about 3pm and got back to Stirling at 6pm.  Ian the friend we had stopped with invited us to stay the night and go out with them.  I find funerals difficult to handle and after a busy week I just wanted to come home.  }{
\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  wasn\rquote t very suited.  I felt a bit bad about not stopping but I just wanted my own bed and a good night\rquote s sleep.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid11670163 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Sun
\par }{\fs24\insrsid11670163 M}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 y brother came and sorted the central heating for us.  Me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 set to and finished scraping the paper off the bedroom.  We were both pleased we had come home last night because we wouldn\rquote t have got them jobs done.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  phoned this afternoon.  He wasn\rquote t feeling too well so I had to go and load a wagon.    
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 
\par Week beginning Monday 28th October
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 The cattle from Stranraer got away without any problems on Saturday so at least something went right.  It looks like things will be busy this week, the order book is fairly full.  There was no wagons left in the
 yard, tonight everything is out.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Tuesday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 We had a visit from Trading Standards today about a ram we had delivered to Buckingham.  We fetched the ram from Lairg in Caithness to our depot, rested it, put it on another wagon and took it down the road. The f
armer met our wagon and took the ram off to save him going down little country lanes with a big wagon.  He told us we had broken the law twice according to DEFRA but in his eyes and from a welfare point of view we had done the job in the best interest of 
the ram.  He was prepared to quash it in this case.  If we had to do everything DEFRA say has to be done and the way it has to be done, we would be unemployed within a month and that's a fact.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Weds
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 It was Newcastleton calf sales today so }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was away there a
nd I was left on my own.  The telephones never stopped all day, it was 9pm before they calmed down.  It is very busy.  It is the busiest day we have had since F&M broke out.  We had 20 vehicles on livestock today, all our own and 6 subcontractors.  It's f
unny, it's nearly 2 year since we have been as busy.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid11670163 L}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 B the Trading Standar
ds Officer phoned today. He had been approached by DEFRA and asked why he had not pressed charges over the ram.  He told them with Armstrong's good reputation and trying to do things right as much as possible, he wasn't going to pursue it and that was the
 end of it.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Thursday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
Longtown was very busy again today.  Vehicles queued on the road right into town.  The only good thing, DEFRA were there to see it for themselves today.  There was a meeting between Longtown mart and DEFRA on Monday to try and get some
 of the restrictions lifted.  They were trying to get them to allow them to use the land rover unloading bay again.  DEFRA in Carlisle couldn't give them a decision.  The answer came from two officials in Page St in London.  What a waste of time.  Two peo
p
le who probably don't know even know where Longtown is, never mind how the market works, making decisions how the market should run.  It's about time these people in Page St got out of London and into the real world.  In the south a big sale is 2 000 head
 of stock, Longtown alone had 9 and a half thousand and Hexham had 8 000.  They can't see sales like this work different to small sales.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid11670163 \page }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Fri
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 The boys that wash the containers didn't turn in this morning so I was washing out all morning.  We needed a few containers today so I just got on and washed five out and got them ready to go.  I was soaked to the skin.
\par 
\par Back in the office this afternoon trying to get caught up.  I got a phone call, }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 's sister is coming down for the week-end but }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  doesn't kn
ow.  It will be a nice surprise for her.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  is also coming this week-end. }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 asked me to work tomorrow but for once in my life I said no.  I haven't had a full week-end off for about 6 week.  I went home about 9pm, }{\fs24\insrsid11670163 [sister]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  landed about 9.30 pm.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281  was nicely surprised.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Saturday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 The Decorator came and measured up today so we went to Carlisle to choose the wallpaper for the bedroom.  We have decided to do the kitchen as well so that the whole house is decorated before we sell it.  We spent all after
noon in Carlisle but we got the paper for both rooms.
\par 
\par We went down to }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 's tonight to see the fireworks but we had to give up after 10 minutes because of the rain.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Sunday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 We had a lazy day today. We didn't do a lot.  I played football in the yard with }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 for a while this morning.  After lunch we went to Asda shopping.  After we came back we lazed about for a while. We took }{\fs24\insrsid11670163 [sister]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 out for their tea tonight before I took }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  up the road.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Week beginning 4}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 th}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  November
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 The cattle set off from Denmark today. They were in Holland this morning where they will rest tonight.  I just hope everything goes to plan after the hassle organising it.
\par Things are very busy in the UK as well, there is a lot of livestock moving but it se
ems to be getting harder. DEFRA have now started following up licences and movements, they were on the phone 3 times today. They are pests when you get them on the phone because you can't get rid of them. But as you would expect they get somebody else to 
do the dirty work for them.  They get Trading standards to follow everything up for them.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par Had an early start this morning both me and }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  were out on wagons this morning.  I was at Lockerbie for 7.30am for a load of sheep into Longtown and }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was lead
ing cattle into Carlisle.  When I got back I was sooner than }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  so I took the phones and started arranging work for today.  }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 got back about 11am and I sent him back out to move some more cattle.  About 2 pm things were getting very busy, the phones wouldn't stop ringing.  I'd just sent }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 to Carlisle to fetch some cattle back.  He was just ready for leaving when I got the phone call I had always dreaded. One of the drivers had tipped a loaded wagon onto its side. It took me a while to get the driver calmed d
own and get any sense out of him.  First thing was to make sure he was all right, then find out where he was.  I caught }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 before he got out of the yard so he jumped in his car with one of our mechanics and took off up the road to him.  This meant I was lef
t with everything to do myself.  The rest of the drivers were very good. They just mucked in, helped with other things so  I could get on.  I was still organising tomorrow's work when }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 got back about 9pm so we set to together and got it sorted. I got finished about 11.30, I didn't need rocking to sleep.
\par 
\par It was one of the busies days we have had, the phones just wouldn't stop ringing. About 6 30 pm I could have could have just walked out and come home.  I still don't know what stopped me from doing it.  I'
ve never felt that way about my job before, I think I'm just sick of the hassle and the rules and regulations.
\par 
\par Wednesday
\par Things starter quieter this morning thank goodness because we didn't have a wagon left in the yard.  By lunch time it was a different 
story, the phones were as bad as ever. It wasn't just as bad because there was 2 of us answering them.  We spent a lot of time finding subcontractors to work for us because we didn't have enough wagons of our own.  I think with the spell of bad weather we
 have had a lot of farmers are getting rid of fat lambs before they damage the ground.  They are appearing from everywhere.  I was hoping for an early finish but I didn't get finished until 9pm.  
\par 
\par Thursday
\par Longtown today but things have quietened down a bit, it wasn't as busy.  There was plenty of sheep about but not a great deal of interest. The abattoirs are full of wet sheep that the vets won't let them kill so they have no room for anymore.
\par 
\par We have started to get sponsors for our karting challenge. Five of us are doing a 2 and a half hour endurance on karts in aid of }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 Marie Curie}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 cancer care. Last year we got to the final at Manchester because we raised the most money in the North of England.  We raised \'a32 700 last year so we are going to try and beat it this year. We need to get on because the race is a week on Sunday.
\par 
\par Friday
\par Not just as busy today so when we had the chance we got caught up on invoices and paperwork. It took nearly all day but we got there eventually.  We got a few more sponsors today so at least we've got a start.
\par 
\par Saturday
\par Started to rub the doors down in the front bedroom today. I managed to get the first two coats of varnish on them while }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  washed the skirting boards and painted them.  Between }{\fs24\insrsid11670163 
[friends]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and dad coming in, it took us all day to get that done.  We had our tea and just relaxed the rest of the night.
\par 
\par Sunday
\par We got woken at 07.00 this morning with the water pipes banging.  With taking the radiator off to paint it, the water wasn't circulating and it boiled and we had
 to run the taps for 20 minutes before it cooled down. Later on I went to Homebase for filler and paint for the radiator.  As soon as I got back I painted the radiator so we could get it back on and the water circulating again.  While I was doing that, }{
\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 was rubbing the doors down again to put another coat of varnish on.  I emulsioned the ceiling while she done that, then put another coat of varnish on the door.  We got cleaned up so now the room is ready for the decorator to come and paper it. 
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Week beginning 11}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 th}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  November
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Out on a wagon most of the day today, some of the day in Scotland and some of the day in England. With working with 2 sets of rules it gets confusing. Do you need a licence or don't you?  Can you do more than one delivery?  In Scot
land the only time you need a licence is for farm to farm movements.  In England all movements need a licence. We get a lot of phone calls from farmers in England who have bought sheep in a Scottish market wanting to know where their paperwork is. So we h
ave to explain to them that you don't need paperwork out of a Scottish market unless the sheep are going to an abattoir.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 's Mum is over at her Mum's in Kilmarnock for a week so }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  has taken a week off work to go up and see them.  It's hard for me
 to get time off at this time of year so I will just have to fend for myself this week.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  is away on another management training day today so I'm left with it again. Things are busy and there are sheep coming our of our ears and with being a wagon
 down it makes things a bit more difficult. I had an odd spare minute or two today.  So I was on the phone getting sponsors for our karting challenge.  Two of the lads in our team drive at night and don't get to see many people so I am trying to fill thei
r sponsor forms as well.
\par 
\par Wednesday
\par It's my birthday today, 21 again "Ha Ha" some}{\fs24\insrsid1444251  }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
days it feels like it but never mind age doesn't bother me.  Age is just what you feel.  Life is what you make it.  The only thing is I think my life went wrong somewhere beca
use all I seem to do is work.  I realise I'm getting older as well. Some days when I come home from work I'm really tired where 15 year ago I could come and get changed, go and have a night out and still work all day the next day.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 caught all the buyers in Longtown today for sponsorship, he done quite well. I went round the offices and garage and caught the drivers as they came in.  I need to have a count up before Sunday se if we can beat last year.  It wasn't just as busy today s
o we got a chance to get some sponsorship.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  came to stay tonight a day early because his Gran was taken into hospital this morning. She is ok but they are going to keep her in for a day or two to keep an eye on her.
\par 
\par Friday
\par We are trying to get organised for the weekend today because we are both away on Sunday and }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 is going to see a new car this afternoon.  He is 40 in January so he is going to treat himself to a Mercedes 4x4.  It's alright for some but he works hard so why not.  He puts more hours in
 than me and I do more than I should but it's different for him. It's his business, I'm just a worker at the end of the day.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid11670163 
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Saturday
\par No lie in to-day. Had to be up and pick the shield up from the engravers and collect one or two sponsor forms.  I went into work and had a count up.  So far we are \'a3
200 short of last year but I still have a fair bit to come in.  I was busy in the house after that - hoovering and washing the kitchen floor.  I fetched the stuff for the Decorator and set things up ready for him.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281  was meant to be going to the pictures with }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 's two nephews. }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 's }{\fs24\insrsid11670163 fianc\'e9e}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 was taking them.  I got }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  ready and we had just finished our tea when the phone rang. }{\fs24\insrsid11670163 [fianc\'e9e]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 had taken ill and Ben asked if I would take them.  I didn't even have time to get changed before we left but never mind it's dark in the pictures. I took them to see the new Harry Potter film and I enjoyed it as much as they did.
\par 
\par Sunday
\par Up early again this morning, the Decorator was meant to come at 09.00 but he didn't turn up until 10.30. I had to leave him at 2 pm to go karting but }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was on her way home.
\par 
\par At the last count before we went we were up to \'a32600 but still had a bit to come in so it looks like we will beat last year's total.  We had a good afternoon  - racing out of 8 teams we were 3}{\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 rd}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
.  The only thing was we all had headaches with the fumes and the coal.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was sick coming home and about 10.30pm I started as well.}{\fs24\super\insrsid13964281    .
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Week beginning 18}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 th}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  November
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 I had a rough night, I didn't settle till 5am this morning.  I didn't get up till 10.30am when }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 woke me.  He is here until tomorrow, he has 2 teacher in service days.  He was fine this morning but I didn't feel well at all. I put the fire on and just laid and slept all day.  I've got no energy at all.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par Off work again still don't feel well.  I don't know whether it was the fumes or a bug or both but I have no energy at all, I just can't get going at all.  I went to Carlisle this afternoon for }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 to get some paint.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  went home this afternoon, he's fine.  When }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 came home from work we went to Carlisle to look for a lampshade.  We didn't see one we liked so we bought a new light instead.
\par 
\par Wednesday
\par Still didn't feel right this morning, stayed off work.  I felt a little better and put the light up in the bedroom so it's nearly finished now.  I phoned Dad to see if he would come and help me. I'm going to surprise }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281  and  tile the kitchen in between the units.  Dad came through just after dinner and we got a start. We just got finished and tidied up when }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 came home from work.  She was surprised and pleased with what we had done.  I didn't do much else the rest of the day. I felt I had done enough because I still didn't feel right, I was tired.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par Back to work today. I still don't feel right but I'm on the mend so I thought I would go back and see.  I had only been back a couple of hours and I was thinking I should have stayed at home, I didn't have a lot of energy, I went to lunchtime.  I had a li
ttle lunch and went back to work and I felt a little better but not right.  I loaded a wagon this afternoon but felt I had maybe done to much. I need to try and get back into work because }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 is going away this weekend and I am on duty.  I just hope it's not too busy, an easy week-end will help me. I got finished about 8 pm and didn't feel 100% but once I had my tea and warmed up I felt better.
\par 
\par Friday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  went away today - that's him away for the week-end. It shouldn't be too bad as it is fairly quiet this week
-end. I am hoping it will be quiet because I still don't feel right.  I got on well today and I am fairly well organised for the week-end so I hoe I won't have to go into work much at all.
\par 
\par Saturday
\par I went into work about 10.00 just to phone men and sort o
ut for Monday.  I had some sheep to deliver into Carlisle abattoir after 12.00 because DEFRA say they can only stay in an abattoir 48 hours before  they are killed, I can't take them in any sooner.  It's crazy, the abattoir has straw pens, food and water.
 
 I know they are going there to be killed but it is more humane on the animal to be comfortable in a straw pen than standing in a market or on a wagon.  With all these rules about F&M, the animal welfare has been lost somewhere along the line. It's time D
EFRA listened to trading standards, farmers, hauliers, markets, basically the people who count.  I didn't get finished until 3.30 pm, longer than what I thought.
\par 
\par Sunday
\par I grouted the tiles in the kitchen today and I am pleased with they way they have turned out, it makes the kitchen look a lot nicer and brighter.
\par 
\par I had to go to work today but just for a couple of hours to put tickets out and make sure everything was right for morning.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid11670163 O}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 ne of the drivers and a good friend of ours asked us to go for a drink
 tonight.  His daughter is 21 today and he is taking her out for a meal so we went up after they had their meal.  I enjoyed the night, we had a quiet drink and a good crack. 
\par }{\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Week 44 beginning 25}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 th}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  November
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Monday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was about today but he left me to it because I knew what was going on. He was sorting some other things out.  For some reason things have gone very quiet.  I don't mind because }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281  is away on a management training day again tomorrow.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par I had a visit off trading standards today, one of our
 part time drivers delivered some sheep into Carlisle 3 week ago and 2 of the sheep were lame.  The man had phoned our driver to warn him but wasn't going to prosecute this time.  Our lad denied driving the wagon.  I couldn't do anything else but tell tra
d
ing standards that he was driving the wagon.  After he had gone I phoned our driver to tell him he was just going to get a warning and just agree with him.  I don't blame him for denying it, I think it's a shame that you can get prosecuted for doing your 
job especially when the rules are different in every county in the country.  Nobody knows whether they are right or wrong.
\par I'm still not feeling too good.  I think I am coming down with flu. Now that's all I need.
\par 
\par Wednesday
\par I feel crap today but }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  is going away to Bedford to the RHA (Road haulage Association) meeting about the new transport guidelines and what we are going to have to do next year.
\par Things are still fairly quiet thankfully because I can't really be bothered but when }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  is away there's nobody else to cover. They will get caught out one day if we are both off together.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par I didn\rquote t feel any better today, I couldn't really be bothered and things are getting busier but I just had to get on with it.  It didn'
t help when the phone rang at 6 am and I had to go into work. I haven't been sleeping well anyway this week. I just went downhill as the day went on. I didn't finish until 10 pm. I didn't feel good at all.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281  and her friend had been late night shopping and they nearly beat me home.
\par 
\par Friday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 was back today and I don't know why but I went to work like the clown I am.  Things are busy again.  It's a 'Rani' Christmas next week as we call it.  It's either a Hindu or Muslim festival so all our coloured [sic
] friends fast for 4 week then have a feast.  They have been fasting for 3 week now so depending on the position of the moon in the sky the feast will be sometime next week so they are buying sheep wherever they can. Why can't they have Christmas the same
 time as everybody else or eat turkey?
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  came to stay today but with things being busy I didn't get finished to 8 pm and I felt lousy.
\par 
\par Saturday
\par I got the car MOT'd this week, it passed no problem thankfully but it wanted a couple of silly little jobs done on it so I took it to the garage and got them done.  After that me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  went for a haircut.

\par We all went to ASDA shopping this afternoon, when we got back and sorted out and had our tea, I felt crap.  I laid on the couch and fell asleep.
\par 
\par Sunday
\par I got up this morning and felt a bit better but a long way off being right.  I sorted the fires and waited for }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 getting up.  We had brunch then we went to Gretna so that }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  could get some presents for his grandparents.  He won't be down before Christmas now, so we took him and got his shopping.
\par 
\par I took }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  up the road after tea. When I got home I didn't do much.  I didn't do much . I still feel crappy - early night and see what tomorrow brings.
