\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\fs24\insrsid13964281 
Back to English rules today in Longtown back to MLC watching you & DEFRA watching them.  Why can Scotland be so advanced and record all movements out of the markets on computer but England can\rquote 
t.  In England you must take a licence before you leave the market but at the same time everything that comes into the market passes through the  market, then leaves the market \endash 
 has to be emailed to DEFRA by the market the day after the sale.  If we could move Longtown market 2 mile north it would save a lot of bother we wouldn\rquote t have half the hassle we have now.
\par 
\par Friday
\par Quite an easy day at work today.  I got a lot of work caught up on for my NVQ.  Hopefully it won\rquote t be too long before my portfolio is complete. Me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  went to Kilmarnock to }{
\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s grandparents tonight.  We are away next weekend so it\rquote s last chance to see them before Xmas.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid11670163 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Sat
\par We went out for lunch with }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s grandparents then went into Kilmarnock, Xmas shopping.
\par 
\par Sun
\par Chilled out.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid11670163 \page }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Monday 9}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 th}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  December
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
This week is going to be busy leading up to Xmas, it always is.  The phones have been going crazy.  As well as the fat sales a lot of farmers who have bought livestock want it home for Christmas.  Because of the rules it makes it a little more difficult w
hen you have a lot of stock to shift.  A lot of the abattoirs now because you can come home to wash out have done away wit their washing facilities.  This makes it very difficult when you are fetching a load back out of the South.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par Things were busy today.  We run out of wagons and drivers fast.  One of the biggest jobs we had today was working out which wagons would be back early enough for tomorrow\rquote s work but we eventually got it sorted out.
\par Just as we were getting ready to go home, an ambulance pulled into the yard.  We hadn\rquote 
t a clue what was going on when we went downstairs we discovered, Stuart, the lad that runs Palletforce had collapsed.  He had gone to move a wagon and had passed out.  He was conscious when the ambulance came and he just wanted
 to go home but the ambulance people wouldn\rquote t let him \endash  they took him to hospital.
\par 
\par Weds
\par I got to work this morning to find a driver walking about with no wagon.  The one he was meant to be going with had broken down.  With the General Haulage being busy a
s well they were short of wagons as well.  After a shuffle about I got him away and not too late.  Just as he was setting off my phone rang, it was }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 .  One of Stampers\rquote 
 small wagons had lifted some cattle on a farm and when he was heading for Carlisle he came towards Westlinton Crossroads and didn\rquote 
t realise the road end was as near as it was and went straight across.  A car hit him half way over and threw it on to its side.  }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 asked me to jump into the van and go and help them get the cattle off the wagon.  We got the cattle off no problem and they were alright. Fortunately there was nobody hurt.  The rest of the day went to plan after all the excitement.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par I had an early start this morning \endash  it was Longtown Christmas fat show today.  We led about 2 and a half thousand sheep into Longtown this morning.  It was the usual gridlock trying to get in and out because of idiots that don\rquote 
t know how the job works.  Although we were busy leading in, we were fairly quiet leading out of the sale.
\par 
\par Fri
\par I was only in work for a couple of hours this morning.  Me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  were going away for the week-end.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote 
s works were having their staff party tonight and we have been invited.  The night out is at Aviemore so we left at lunchtime.  We arrive about 3.30 pm and
 booked into the hotel and dropped our stuff off in our room.  Then we went and met the rest of them for coffee.  We had a great night and I really enjoyed it.  It was strange though as we were told we had to pay for nothing.  I\rquote 
m that used to paying for what I get but I wasn\rquote t complaining.
\par 
\par Sat
\par We left Aviemore about 11am and as we had plenty of time (for a change) we called in at Pitlochry.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  has never been up that side of the country before so
 I took the chance to let her see some of it while we had the chance.  Took }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 to the dam so she could see the salmon ladder and watch the salmon.  After that we had a walk round the shops in Pitlochry.  We left there and came farther down \endash  on the way down we called in at Ballinluig \endash 
 we went to the graveyard because I wanted to call in and see }{\fs24\insrsid484382 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s grave and spend a minute or two with an old friend.  We left there and went down to Glasgow where we spent the night with }{
\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s sister.
\par 
\par Sun
\par We didn\rquote t get up too early this morning.  Margaret was at work so we had breakfast then we went to Braehead shopping centre to finish off our Xmas shopping.  We walked about there for an hour or two then went back to Margaret\rquote s.  Mag\rquote 
s was home from work so we stopped and had our tea with her before we came home.  I enjoyed my week-end away \endash  it\rquote s quite a while since I\rquote ve been as relaxed.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Monday 16}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 th}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  December
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Back to the grind this morning.  I could have stopped in bed this morning although it was a good relaxing week-end, it was hectic.  }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 had decide to sell the continental containers and stop going abroad with livestock.  There is too much hassle involved organising loads abroad and since }{\fs24\insrsid484382 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 has gone, there is nobody really interested in going abroad.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par Things 
are very busy but it seems to be the middle of the week.  Because of the regulations and the time livestock can be kept after it has been sold, abattoirs do most of the killing in the middle of the week.  There are 2 types of sales in England, one week is
 
a store sale and the next week is a designated slaughter sale.  If you buy stock in a store sale you can take it home and send it to an abattoir or you can take it home for a week then send it direct to an abattoir and does not affect your 21 days that yo
u
 are meant to keep them.  A designated slaughter day means the livestock has to go direct to the abattoir.  If a farmer bought livestock last week, nothing is allowed on or off his land for 21 days but on a designated slaughter day he can still sell his f
a
t stock even if he bought stock last week.  So he could sell fat stock today even if he bought stock last week.  When the stock gets to the abattoir it must be killed within 48 hours. So with most sales being mid week most of the abattoirs have to fill th
eir orders when they can which is the middle of the week when the livestock is available. 
\par 
\par Weds
\par Things are very busy today \endash  there is a lot of livestock about.  The Pakistani abattoirs are stocking up taking sheep to local farms to keep for over Christmas because of their religion they don\rquote 
t celebrate the same as we do.  They are keeping us busy because we are doing some of next week\rquote s work this week.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par Early start this morning leading sheep into Longtown.  We have to make sure we count the sheep ex
actly right.  DEFRA now are clamping down on numbers that are put on the licence.  If you load sheep on a farm for example if you go for 150 and you load them out of a corner of a field it\rquote 
s nearly impossible to get a correct count. You might 149 but when 
you get to the market where you can count them properly and there is 148 but you have written 149 on the licence, DEFRA want to know where the other sheep is.  You are not allowed to be human, you can\rquote t make a mistake, you\rquote 
ve got to be the same as DEFRA and live in a perfect world where mistakes don\rquote t happen.  I would like to see some of these people in a field counting sheep because I don\rquote 
t think they would know where to start.  They expect every farm to have pens and runs and loading banks for sheep.  Real life doesn\rquote t work that way.  Normal people don\rquote 
t have the money.  The Government does so they have to make do with what they have got and what they can afford.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  came down tonight.  He is staying with me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  until after Christmas.
\par 
\par Fri
\par Things are quieter today there isn\rquote t so much moving today but we are expecting a rush at the beginning of next week.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was at work with me this morning.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281  came at 11a to take him to the Doctors.  He has a touch of bronchitis. That is }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  finished to New Year now \endash  lucky for some.  Sunday\rquote s work didn\rquote 
t take a lot of sorting out. We are starting to think it might not be as busy as we thought.
\par 
\par Sat
\par Up fairly early this morning.  I wanted to go to Carlisle to get }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s Xmas present and get back before it was too busy.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and }{
\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  went with me and when we got to Carlisle, me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  went one way and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  another.  Me and }{
\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  went and got what we wanted then went and met up with }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 .  We went and got some things for }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote 
s Parents to take over to Islay with us.  We went to see my Mam and Dad when we were in Carlisle, we stayed there for a while before we came home.
\par 
\par Sunday
\par We got up early this morning and went to ASDA thinking if we were early we would miss the busy time.  We were wrong. I\rquote ve never seen it as busy. It took us 3 hours to get round and get our shopping.  I\rquote 
m looking forward to Christmas not just because it\rquote s Xmas but I\rquote m on holiday. I\rquote m looking forward to the break and feel I\rquote m ready for a holiday.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Monday 23 rd December}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281     
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 It wasn\rquote t as busy as we expected today, I think everyone got what they wanted last week.  I\rquote 
m not complaining though a couple of quiet days will help me to get caught up on paperwork.  I spent really all day catching up and trying to get ahead as much as I can so I haven\rquote t got too much to do when I come back in the New Year.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par Only 1 wagon out today so I got on well and got all my office work up to date.  I finished at lunch time because there was nothing else to do.  I helped }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 to clean the house and get things ready so we could chill out for a couple of days.  The only thing we have 
to do tomorrow is cook the dinner And enjoy ourselves.  My brother has built a kart with an engine on it for his kids so he has put it in one of my garages until tomorrow.
\par 
\par Weds
\par We had a lie in this morning despite }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  being excited last night, he didn\rquote t
 get up until 9.30am this morning.  We had the fires on and the breakfast made before he got up.  It was good to see the look  on his face as he was opening his presents.  }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 Brother}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 came round with his 2 kids and we went down to the yard so they could drive about with the kart.  After dinner we just chilled out.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par It was raining today but we didn\rquote t mind we just lazed about all day.
\par 
\par Friday
\par Up early this morning, we are dropping }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  off at home and then catching the lunch time ferry.  We are going to Islay for New year.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 was quite happy about going home this time because Santa had been there as well.  We arrived at Islay about 4.30 pm, everybody was in good wind.  We sat about and caught up on the gossip.
\par 
\par Sat
\par I was helping }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 A}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  today he was puttin
g up a new fence round the sheep pens so we dug all the post holes and concreted the posts in.  It made a nice change to be out of the office doing something different and no telephones.
\par 
\par Sun
\par Me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  went to Bowmore to the home today to take }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote 
s Gran her Xmas presents and to see her.  She was pleased to see us and looked well, the best I\rquote ve seen her for a while.  I hope I never get to the stage I have to live in a home. I feel sorry for people who live homes it\rquote 
s just an existence.  We came back to Cladach and just chilled.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Mon 30}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 th}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  December
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 I helped }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 A}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 again today.  We put the rails on the fence so we could fetch the sheep in and dose them.  In the afternoon we fetched the sheep in and dosed them for worms and liver fluke.  I enjoyed myself, it\rquote 
s a long time since I have worked with sheep this way.  After we had got the sheep done, I done a few repairs on }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 A}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s pick up.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 A}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was away doing his deliveries today so I just chilled out.  It was cold and windy outside so I wasn\rquote t bothered.  I just lazed about and had a lazy day.
\par 
\par Weds New Year\rquote s Day
\par Didn\rquote t get up very early today. We didn\rquote t get to bed until 5.30 am this morning despite having a quiet night.  We stayed in the house to see the New Year in.  On the stroke of midnight }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 A}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 was outside and shot both barrels of the shotgun into the air.  It\rquote s an old tradition on the Islands, it\rquote s supposed to ward off all evil and bad for the coming year.  Willie and Chrissie came down and then later on }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 
[son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 , the man from next door came in.  We didn\rquote t do a lot after we got up, just laid about and slept but we are going to the New Year\rquote s dance tonight.     
\par 
\par Thursday
\par Definitely didn\rquote t get up very early today.  The dance didn\rquote t start until 10 pm and with }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote 
s Mam being on the Hall committee we were there to the finish.  It was a good night, we saw a lot of people we haven\rquote t seen for a long time and caught up on what\rquote 
s been going on.  I enjoyed the night despite feeling a bit low today, too much booze and lack of sleep.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  went to see one of her friends today but I just laid about and done nothing.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 \page }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Fri
\par Didn\rquote t do a lot today, we went to see }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s Gran  before we go home as we go home tomorrow.  On the way back from Bowmore, we called in to see }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s Aunty and Uncle.  It was about 8pm by the time we got back.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s Mam had got }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote 
s cot out of the loft and one or two baby things that }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and her sister had used when they were babies.  We sat with }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote 
s Mam trying to choose names.
\par 
\par Sat
\par We left Islay at lunchtime and got to the mainland about 5.30pm. I didn\rquote 
t want to leave as the weather was so good.  We got home about 9.30pm. I have never known our house to be as cold.  We put on both fires and the calor gas fire. We sat with our coats on f
or the first hour. It was so cold upstairs we never unpacked either. My brother was looking after the house for us but being as thick as he is he never thought to put the fire on for us.
\par 
\par Sun
\par The house was a little warmer this morning but still cold.  I cleaned both fires out and got them going but it was nearly tea time before the heat was getting through the house.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 unpacked while I took the decorations down and put them away. Ann, }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s friend called on her way home from work so she stayed and had tea with us. I\rquote 
m sitting now about 9.30pm writing my diary and it\rquote s the first time the house has felt anywhere near warm since we got home.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Week 50/6}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 th}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  January
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Things started off slowly today so this morning I got all the paperwork for the tippers done and all the notes from the week-end done.  Things started to pick up in the afternoon but not too busy just steady.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par Two of the young lads that work in the yard are on a Young Apprentice Scheme and Young Drivers\rquote  Scheme and I have been appointed
 as their Monitor.  Their assessor was here today so I was in a meeting  with them for a while today.  I am going for a day in two weeks time at the training centre.  I am going to be assessing for them on Livestock Transport. On one hand I\rquote 
m looking forward to it, on the other I\rquote m a bit apprehensive.
\par 
\par Weds
\par Things are fairly busy today on top of our usual work, we are restocking a farm at Southwaite.  For some reason we have had a few enquiries lately about restocking.  It\rquote s surprising how many farms are still to restock so long after F&M.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par  Busy again today.  Longtown fat day and they have a lot of sheep in.  We run out of wagons fast today \endash  everybody is looking for sheep and with prices being good, everybody\rquote s getting rid of them.  I think things
 will go quiet after January because sheep will run out.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 \page }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Friday
\par Not a lot doing today so I done some training with }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [boys]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  for their apprenticeship.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  came today.  I haven\rquote t seen him since Xmas so I was looking forward to him coming to stay.
\par 
\par Saturday
\par We went to Carlisle today.  We went to order the pram and to get one or two things for the baby coming.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  is getting bigger now and we are both looking forward to junior\rquote s arrival.  }{
\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was sitting tonight feeling }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s tummy and the baby moving.
\par 
\par Sun
\par We had an easy day today.  We didn\rquote t do a lot.  I spent the day with }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  playing games with him and just spending time with him when I had the chance.
\par When I got back from taking }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  up the road, }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and B}{\fs24\insrsid16677158  }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 were in.  They had the P}{\fs24\insrsid16677158 S}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281 2 on and were playing Colin McCrae rally.  They were there unto midnight.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Week 51 \endash  13}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 th}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  January
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 I was a bit busier this morning, we are back up to 3 tippers so there is more DLY notes and more info to put into the computer.  Things are fairly busy on the livestock side as well as everybody is still looking for sheep \endash 
 demand is good.  I just hope the supply is still there to keep it going.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par I was out on a wagon this morning just doing local work in and around Cumbria.  I enjoy getting out.  You get sick of looki
ng out of the window and looking at the same thing.  I also like to get out because you have no hassle, no telephones ringing at the time.
\par 
\par Weds
\par Busy today, there is sheep coming out of the woodwork everywhere.  I won\rquote t know what they are going to do when they start double tagging sheep.  They will never keep a track of things \endash  I just can\rquote t see it working.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was away at a meeting today with the Cumbria Welfare Liaison group.  They fetched the point up about double tagging sheep not being possible
.  They were told by Defra that he papers had already been signed so it would have to happen.  They said that they knew it wouldn\rquote 
t work but because somebody in Page St had agreed and signed the papers, it would have to be done. This is a prime example of Defra not listening to the people that count.
\par 
\par Friday
\par Not so busy again today \endash  a good chance to get caught up with paperwork.  We heard a whisper today that the rules are going to change.  They are going to do away with the 20 day rule and cut it to six d
ays.  We had heard rumours about this but there is going to be an announcement next week.  We also heard that there might be some rules attached to this but we can\rquote t find out what they are.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 \page }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Sat
\par I didn\rquote t do a lot today.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  went to Carlisle with her friend.  I stayed at home, done some housework for }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and had a g}{\fs24\insrsid16677158 o}
{\fs24\insrsid13964281  on the P}{\fs24\insrsid16677158 S}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 2.  }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 M}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 y friend was in for an hour so we had a coffee and a crack.
\par It is our works dance tonight so I don\rquote t think I\rquote ll be very fit in the morning.
\par 
\par Sun
\par We had a good night last night. Everybody mixed together, no arguments or fall outs.  It was a good night.  I was up this morning and had breakfast.  I suppose there\rquote s a first time for everything.  I wasn\rquote 
t feeling that good though.  I laid about all day \endash  just tired I think.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Week 52 \endash  20}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 th}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  January
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281  Out on a wagon today leading sheep and cattle into Carlisle. I didn\rquote t get back unto lunchtime.  I called in at home because }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 had been o the phone.  There was a letter from the tax office.  I have had a bill off the tax man for underpaid tax from the F&M.  It\rquote 
s never ending, I sometimes wonder if I will ever get away from F&M.  I fell out with them at work over it because it\rquote s their fault for not working the tax out right in the first place.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par I was trying to sort this mess with my tax out today but I\rquote m not getting very far.  Nobody at work seems to want to know about it.  I told them today to stick their van and not to bother asking me to go anywhere fro them again.
\par 
\par Weds
\par I tried to keep out of the office today. I\rquote ve just lost al interest in my job.  I\rquote m going on a course tomorrow about assessing people from outside of our company.  I\rquote m not in the right frame of mind for going because if this isn
\rquote t sorted out they will be told to stick that as well.  I don\rquote t want to say too much yet because }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  is 40 this week end and he is going away for a few days.  I don\rquote 
t want to spoil his week-end but when he comes back \'93the shit will hit the fan.\'94
\par 
\par Thursday
\par Away on a course today and I quite enjoyed it but part of me wanted to do it and the part said why should I bother.  At the end of the day it means more work for me but I feel now why should I help the company when they can\rquote t help me.  I think it
\rquote s bad, 16 years I\rquote ve been here.  I\rquote ve helped them as much as I can for them to turn round and shrug their shoulders when  have a problem that is their fault.
\par 
\par Friday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  is away for the week-end. He went away this morning, the atmosphere was a bit dry before he went.  I done as little as possible the rest of the day.  I couldn\rquote 
t be bothered.  I done what was needed so I don\rquote t have to go in much over the week-end.
\par The new rules were announced in the farming papers today.  The 20 day rule has been 
replaced by a six day rule.  This is good.  It will help the job a lot.  The other thing is they say they are going to put a vet in every market and any livestock sold through a market can only travel 150 km.  If they get that rule in, there will be no li
vestock industry left.
\par 
\par Sat
\par }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  is down for the week-end but I only had to go to work for an hour or so today. I went this morning because my brother is coming to wire the lights up in the kitchen cabinets today.
\par 
\par After my brother had been we went to ASDA shopping, the we took }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  to MacDonalds for tea.  Chilled out the rest of the night.
\par 
\par Sun
\par I had to go to work for 2 or 3 hours today.  A few more orders came in yesterday so I had to go and get some wagons ready and phone drivers to let them know what they were doing in the morning.
\par I sat this afternoon and played games with }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  before taking him up the road.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 
\par 
\par Wk 53 - Monday 27}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 th}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  January
\par }\pard\plain \s15\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\insrsid13964281 
Usual Monday today. I have paperwork today with having three tippers back on again. Everybody is talking about the new 6 day rule and how it\rquote s going to effect everybody.  There\rquote s a lot of meetings everywhere this week about the 6 day rule.

\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\fs24\insrsid13964281 
\par Tuesday
\par The pho
nes were busy today, people asking what the new rules are and when they are coming in and how they will affect them.  The rules that are coming into place, instead of of 20 day standstill if you stock onto your farm, they are going to reduce it to 6 days.
  That\rquote 
s the good part.  The bad part is that markets will have to make sure everything is washed before leaving the market.  They are also talking about anything bought in a market will be only allowed to travel 150km/94 mile.  If they make this rule stick
 the agriculture industry is finished.
\par 
\par Weds
\par We are busy today \endash  middle of the week always is busy now with everything having to be killed within 48 hours so most of the abattoirs want everything in the middle of the week.  For meat to flavour properly it 
should be hung for at least a week but these days it\rquote s packaged the next day, ready for the shelf, then delivered to supermarkets within two days.  That\rquote s the time they give it t mature.  So if you buy sheep on a Wednesday, it\rquote 
s killed on a Thursday, packed on a Friday, in the shops on a Monday. This is where Defra doesn\rquote t understand, they think it\rquote s bought and in the supermarket the same day.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par There was quite a lot of sheep in Longtown today, things are quite busy. All the drivers are talking about the new rules and especially the movement of 150 km out of markets. }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 is going away in the morning. He is going to London fr a meeting. It is the R.H.A. AGM so he wants to go and see if he can find out just what is going to happen.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 \page }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Friday
\par Not as busy today, more store stock moving about than fat at the end of the week.  }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  went away about lunch time \endash 
 he was going to call in on one or two customers on the way down the road.  Although it was fairly quiet today, it was still 8 pm when I got finished and the phone didn\rquote t stop ringing to 11pm.
\par 
\par Sat
\par I was in work to lunch time today trying to get sorted for Sunday and Monday. I went home and done very little.
\par 
\par Sun
\par Ended up going to work today for a couple of hours to get wagons ready for morning because there was more work come in last night and this morning.  I didn\rquote t do a lot this afternoon \endash  I couldn\rquote t be bothered.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Wk 54 - Monday  3}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 rd}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  February
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Busy day today catching up with paperwork.  Computers are supposed to make life easier but I think they make it harder because you have to back everything up on paper.  }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 was telling me about his meeting and things don\rquote t look good at all.  The 6 day rule is coming in in March and they are going to review it in May.  Whichever one }{\fs24\ul\insrsid13964281 they }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
think is working best, will be put
 in place and stay in place.  All M.L.C. staff who look after the washing out at markets are finished at the end of February and it will be up to the markets to police the cleansing of vehicles.  If a dirty vehicle turns up with livestock to sell, it will
 
have to be turned away at the entrance (still with stock on).  The public car park also has to be policed the same way. In August the 150 km out of markets is coming in, the government say because there are no fat markets in Europe and stock is traded on 
the farm.  Britain has to come in line with the rest of Europe. If yu go to Greece or Spain on holiday, you can see full carcasses hanging outside of a butcher\rquote 
s shop, their abattoirs are a disgrace. Is it not about time the rest of Europe practice what they preach and come up to standards as well. 
\par Tuesday
\par We had a driver hand in his notice today, he is going to another livestock haulier. He says it\rquote s because it\rquote s more money and the way the industry is.  He thinks the way we work compared the way he works, there\rquote 
s more chance of staying in work longer.  We think he is wrong but everybody to their own.  If they make all these new rules stick, we will be all out of a job along with everybody else connected with agriculture.
\par 
\par Weds
\par Busy day today, there is a \lquote Paki\rquote  [sic] festival next week so there is a lot of ewes about.  Our ethnic cousins are buying them and stock piling them on farms.  These festivals are not on a set date \endash 
 it all depends where the moon is in the sky.  Sheep are getting more expensive, for some reason so there is a lot about.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par Started early this morning loading sheep into Longtown.  It was frosty, I was frozen. Got the sheep into Longtown then went into the canteen for breakfast to get warmed up.  All the talk in the market was about the new rules and how they can\rquote 
t work. The feeling is that if the new rules do come in, agriculture as we know it will be finished.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 \page }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Friday
\par It was busier than normal for a Friday. Today we were shifting a lot of store livestock about. There is quite a lot of store and breeding sales just now. }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  came down tonight for the week-end but I didn
\rquote t get finished until 8.30 pm.
\par 
\par Sat
\par I went into work for a couple of hours today.  When I came home I set to and washed the kitchen ceiling and the walls.  Hopefully the decorator will be here in the next couple of weeks.
\par 
\par Sunday
\par We went to Carlisle today and got a new curtain rail and bits and pieces for the kitchen. We just chilled out and I spent some time with }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  before I took him home.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Wk 55 - Monday 10}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 th}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  February
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 We had another driver hand in his notice today.  He is going to work for the Edinburgh Woollen Mill.  He says he can\rquote 
t see any future in driving a livestock vehicle.  There is a few more drivers that are uneasy about the way things are going.  The trouble is there\rquote s nothing we can tell them to assure them.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par I was out on a wagon this morning with one driver leaving on Friday, we\rquote re a little bit short.  Things are busy, we haven\rquote t been as busy as this since F&M broke out.  We will be a container down by this week end as we have sold one.  We don
\rquote t know whether to order a new one or not but we will have to do something with us being as busy.
\par 
\par Weds
\par Very busy today, we have all our own wagons and 5 subcontractors. I don\rquote t know how we got through all the work but we did \endash  just!  We said today if double tagging and 150km rule comes in how are we going to be able to move anything?  It
\rquote s alright trading everything direct off farm but it takes twice as long to move it.  We can\rquote t keep up now, how will we manage if that happens?  I would like to see so
me of the ones making these rules to come and sit in our office for one day and see how hard it is to organise and follow some of the stupid rules.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par Out on a wagon today leading into Longtown, then delivering and picking up livestock locally.  We were loading wagons most of the afternoon. }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 is going tomorrow to see one of our biggest customers and if it goes well he is going to call in and order a new container.  We decided the only thing to do is keep going forward.
\par 
\par Friday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  came down last night. He has got his half term break, he is her until Tuesday.  I was hoping to be off work on Monday and Tuesday so I could spend some time with }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281 .  The Boss of the company }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was going to see phoned this morning and cancelled his meeting. He put if off unto Monday. I was a bit miffed. }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281  was going to cancel this meeting but me being a soft bugger, told him not to cancel it.  He went and ordered a new container today, despite not having his meeting.
\par 
\par Sat
\par Great \endash  first time for a while I didn\rquote t have t go to work. I painted the back kitchen ceiling today. }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  bought me a DVD for Valentine\rquote 
s Day so we sat and watched the film.  It was good to sit and do nothing and just relax.
\par 
\par Sun
\par I spent most of the day with }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 , just messing about on the playstation.  We took }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  to Glasgow tonight as her Dad was coming to Paisley with cattle so }{
\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  is going home with him for a week as it will be the last chance before the baby is born.
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Wk 56 - Monday 17}{\b\fs24\super\insrsid13964281 th}{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281  February
\par }\pard\plain \s15\qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\insrsid13964281 Up early this morning. I took }{\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\insrsid13964281  to my Mam\rquote 
s for the day, it\rquote s not fair to take him to work not knowing what time I will get finished.
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 was away in North Wales today to see one of our biggest customers. ASDA h
ave told them they will need to make their meat a little cheaper so they are trying to cut the price of haulage.  I just hope them at ASDA appreciate that since Blair and Bush decided to hassle Sadam, fuel has gone up 4p a litre.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par Off work today, I glossed the window sill and the skirting boards in the kitchen this am. I spent the afternoon with }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 before taking him up the road.  It was good to be able to spend as much time with him.
\par 
\par Weds
\par I had an early start this morning. I went to pick some ca
ttle up near Hexham. The farm I picked the cattle up on was in the middle of nowhere on top of a hill. The farmer was telling me they had a visit off the Minister for Agriculture last summer. He was there for the campaign to stop hunting.  They showed him
 their books for the last 5 year.  They\rquote ve gone from 10 000 a year profit to 4 000 last year. The Minister told them the best thing they could do was give up. If that\rquote 
s the attitude of the Government, we might as well give up now and let the countryside grow wild.  If we done that 10 year down the line, they\rquote 
ll be paying farmers to put animals back on the land to keep the countryside from growing wild.  If we take all the animals away, there\rquote ll be nowhere for people to walk and go and see because it will be grown over.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par Very busy again today. I was out on a wagon all morning with being two drivers down, we\rquote re just struggling a bit.  We put an advert in the paper last week and we\rquote ve had quite a good response but we haven\rquote t found anybody with the right
 experience yet.  It\rquote s not a job just anybody can do and with as many people going out of agriculture you have to take people without experience and train them.
\par 
\par Fri
\par I finished early today, I went to Glasgow to meet }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  off the plane.  She came home from her Mam\rquote s and Dad\rquote 
s this afternoon. The pane was delayed 2 hours so I had to hang about in the airport for 2 hours.  When she arrived, we went to Kilmarnock, we are going to spend the week-end with her grandparents.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 \page }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Sat
\par We took }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s grandparents to
 Troon for their lunch and on the way back we called at the garden centre to get papa his compost for his tomato plants.  I just sat and watched the rugby this afternoon.
\par 
\par Sun
\par We went today and got some things for when the baby arrives, }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s Aunty gave us a crib so we went and got a quilt and bumper set for it.  We also got all the things for the cot.  That\rquote 
s us just about got everything now all we need is Junior to come now.  After we had our tea we headed home and just relaxed the rest of the night.
\par 
\par  
\par }\pard\plain \s1\qj \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\f1\fs24\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid13964281 Week 57
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\fs24\insrsid13964281 
Just the usual Monday today catching up with paperwork in the morning.  Things got a little bit busy in the afternoon but not too bad.  We are still trying to get our heads round the new changes that are coming in.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\qj \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\insrsid13964281 Tuesday
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\fs24\insrsid13964281 Out on a wagon today I
 took a load of sheep to Stirling. We are still short of drivers but the response to the advert in the paper has been good.  }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  is going to do some interviews this week and see if we can get someone started.

\par 
\par Weds
\par Back in the office this morning, things are
 busy for the time of year.  We wonder sometimes where all the livestock is coming from.  Prices are very god just now so its encouraging people to sell stock rather than keep hold of it until prices get better.  It\rquote 
s a good sign that prices are good becau
se a lot of farmers were just trying with about 60% of the stock pre F&M to se how things were going to do so with things being good and going well it will encourage them to stock back 100% rather than go down the way.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par I was leading sheep into Longtown today. It\rquote 
s the first sale under the new rules.  What a nightmare.  The whole place was at a standstill.  After you have emptied your sheep off you have to wash the wheels at the wash then drive over another wheel wash but you can still come out of 
the auction without washing the container out.  The muck inside the container must not be able to carry the disease!
\par 
\par Friday
\par Not quite as busy today.  I went to Silloth for a load of fertilizer.  Spring is in the air and farmers are looking for something to make the grass grow.  It\rquote 
s nice when the lambs are out in the fields you know spring is coming and hopefully good weather.
\par 
\par Saturday
\par }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  is here for the weekend so I\rquote m not working today.  We went into town this morning to get a few more things ready for baby coming.  We\rquote re getting there slowly but there\rquote 
s a lot we need now.  We took }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  to McDonalds on the way home for a treat.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 \page }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Sunday
\par Went shopping today then came home and took most of the things out of the kitchen because the decorator is coming next week.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s2\qj \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs24\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\insrsid13964281 Week 58
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\fs24\insrsid13964281 
Things started quiet this morning.  I got caught up on paperwork.  We had a new man started this morning so I went with him to Stirling and Perth just to give him some training and show him how the job worked.  He is a lad about 25 years 
old.  He had worked on his Uncle\rquote s farm since he left school.  He has worked 7 days a week ever since.  With the way farming has gone his Uncle could only afford to pay him \'a3
200 per week so he got out.  He come to work with us because he still wanted a connection with agriculture.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par Back on a wagon today. I went to a farm at Hesket Newmarket with fertilizer and then went to Silloth for another load.  It was wet and windy, I was a bit sick by the time I had got loaded and roped and sheeted.
\par 
\par Weds
\par I took a load of cattle into Carlisle this morning.  The rules there are not quite as strict as Longtown.  It seems the same as it has been from the start.  There is more officials in some markets than others and some officials are more strict than others
.  You get to know what markets you can do what in.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par Early start this morning. I had 2 load of sheep to take into Longtown.  It was the same farce as last week.  Longtown are getting short of yard staff because of the rules it is making it so much 
harder for the staff to move the sheep and get them in the right place.  They have just had enough most of them go to the market one or two days a week just for a second income to keep them going.  Now they are stopping at home because it\rquote 
s less hassle.  Somebody is going to have to sort this out or there will be nobody left.
\par 
\par Fri
\par Went to Silloth again this morning for a load of fertilizer.  It is a very busy place at the moment.  There is orders for 2500 ton all to be delivered in March.
\par I finished early tonight because it\rquote s the annual cow punchers ball.  This is the nickname it has been given over the years.  It\rquote 
s right title is Animal Road Haulage Association Northern Division Annual Dinner Dance.  So you can understand why it\rquote s been shortened to the cowp
unchers.  Apart from the band it was a good night.  I seen a lot of faces I only see at that dance, hauliers from Yorkshire and Lancashire.  I speak to them often enough on the phone but it\rquote 
s nice to put a face to the voice and have a natter with them.
\par 
\par Saturday
\par We didn\rquote t do a lot today.  We didn\rquote t get up very early and when we did, }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote 
s back was aching a bit with sitting so long last night.  She is getting quite big now so she gets a bit uncomfortable.  I sat and watched the rugby this afternoon and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 had 40 winks on the couch.  It was nice to see her chilling out because normally she never stops.
\par 
\par Sun
\par The decorator finally came this morning but not to start.  He is coming on Tuesday night.  He is going to do it at night after work so we can get it
 finished and back to normal before the baby arrives.  I gave all the bits that needed it another coat of gloss this afternoon and so everything is ready for him coming now.
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Week 59
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Early start this morning we have a driver away on a hazardous goods cours
e and another on holiday.  I took a load of cattle to Stirling this morning and then went to Perth to fetch a load of sheep back.  I enjoyed my day.  It made a nice change to get out of the office.  There was only myself to worry about no telephones.  I j
u
st did what I had to do and came home.  I think also getting out and seeing the countryside and different things rather than sitting looking at a computer screen and 4 walls.  When I am in the office I look out of the window and see the same things every 
time.  When I\rquote m out on a wagon I see something different all the time.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par I took a load of sheep into Longtown this morning, then went to Silloth for a load of ferty (fertiliser).  We are doing quite a lot of ferty now because the livestock is quieting off a little bit.  It\rquote 
s still amazing just how busy the livestock is for the time of year and considering the amount of livestock that was killed through F&M.
\par Ian the Decorator phoned this afternoon because he is having to work late.  I am beginning to think he will never get this kitchen decorated.
\par 
\par Weds
\par I was delivering sheep around the Penrith area today to various farms.  I enjoyed that going to farms and talking to the farmers  Most of them are optimistic about the future the way things are at the mo
ment.  The only thing they said was and they all said it if Defra are sensible and don\rquote t keep coming with stupid rules and use some common sense farming still has a chance.
\par I got a shock when I got home.  Ian had actually turned up and started to decorate the kitchen.  Ian went home about 8pm and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 started to make the tea.  While she was making the tea, her waters started to leak.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  phoned the hospital and had to take her I to get checked because she still has 6 weeks to go.  When we got to the h
ospital }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was checked over but they couldn\rquote t say whether all her waters had gone or just some but whatever the baby could be 2 to 3 weeks early.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281  had an injection to help the baby\rquote s lungs develop faster because she was going to give birth earlier than what she should.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 had to stay in hospital for the night so they could keep an eye on her and to give her the second part of the injection in the morning.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par I got a phone call at 7am to say that they thought }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was going into labour.  When I got to the hospital }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 was having contractions.  At 12.12 pm we had a little girl 6 weeks early.  She was quite a good weight for being early 4lb 14 oz but very small.  She was take away to the special care baby unit.  When we got to see he
r she was on oxygen and pipes and monitors all around her.  We were told not to worry it was all precaution because she was early and with no explanation.  It\rquote s hard not to worry when you see all them pipes and machines.
\par 
\par Friday
\par Went into hospital this morning and }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  (that\rquote s the name we\rquote 
ve decided for the baby) was off all the machines.  She just had a drip in the back of her hand feeding her.  I went up town and got a few last minute things that we hadn\rquote t got seeing as }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 had caught us out.  I went and picked Mam up and took her to the hospital to see her granddaughter.  Mam came home with me this afternoon to stay with the Decorator while I went for }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
.  I was just having a cup of coffee with Ian when }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s M
