\par Week 61   }{\fs24\insrsid13964281     
\par Things are still busy at work.  I don\rquote t know where all the livestock comes from.  I was out on a wagon for a while today but I don\rquote t want to go to far in case I have to go to the hospital.  I finished quite early so I could go and see }{
\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 .
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par Out on a wagon again today.  I\rquote ve never known it as busy for this time of year.  People are starting to move animals out to grass after wintering so that is to do as well.  I like them jobs.  It\rquote 
s nice to see cattle galloping and jumping across the fields after spending so long stuck in sheds.  I finished early again.  They have asked }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  to stop in hospital with }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]
}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  tonight and see how she gets on with feeding.  I didn\rquote t leave the hospital until midnight.  }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was still hungry so the nurses topped her up through a tube.
\par 
\par Weds
\par In the office today trying to get caught up on the paperwork and one of the young lads I have been training has got his theory test for his car 
today.  I spent a lot of the morning with him testing him on his highway code and learning him.  He phoned this afternoon. He passed so that\rquote s good.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  phoned this morning. She didn\rquote t have a very good night.  When the nurse topped }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  up last night she took her back to the ward so  that }{
\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  could get some sleep.  She told the other nurse that }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was to wake up at 04.00 when }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 was due to be fed.  The other nurse misunderstood the first one and fed }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  at 04.00.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was a bit upset because she is trying so hard  to get }{
\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  feeding and putting weight on so there might be a chance  of getting her home.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 couldn't stop in tonight  because the rooms were both booked.  A night's sleep at home will do her good.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par Early start this morning leading sheep into Longtown.  It was a busy day in Longtown today.  There was a lot of sheep in.  I sat for nearly three quarter\rquote s of an hour waiting to get out of the market.  The queue was that big to get in I couldn
\rquote t get out.
\par }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  is stopping at the hospital again tonight. }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  hasn\rquote 
t been fed through her tube since 10.30 this morning. I spent the evening at hospital with them both and didn\rquote t come home until midnight.  
\par 
\par Fri
\par Just in the office today but I finished early.  I went to Abington and picked }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  up.  We came home, had a shower, got changed and off to the hospital.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 got to cuddle his little sister tonight.  She is doing well.  She has fed off }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  since yesterday morning.  They weighed her this morning but she hasn\rquote t put any weight on but she hasn\rquote 
t lost any.  The nurse said that was normal with her feeding o}{\fs24\insrsid16677158 n}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  her own and being so small she burns up a lot of calories feeding but it was good because she hasn\rquote t lost any weight either.
\par 
\par Sat
\par Me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  got up this morning and done some washing and done some housework before we went to the hospital.  We went to the hospital to see }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and }{
\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  then we went and picked the pram and done a bit of shopping.  I don\rquote t know if anybody else reads the diaries but we bumped into C on the way into town.  We stood and talked for a while about 
}{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and discussed the diaries.  C was debating whether to go and get her hair cut because she looked a mess.  There was
 nothing wrong with the way she looked.  We went and got our bits and bobs then went back to the hospital for an hour.  Me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 came home to let the pets out and so I could fetch the washing in.  While we were at home }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  phoned.  They have asked her to take the car seat in.  They haven\rquote t said }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 
[new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  will be able to come home but it looks promising.  With }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  being premature they have to put her in the car seat for a while and monitor her breathing.  
\par 
