\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\fs24\insrsid13964281 Back to work this morning back to the usual delivery notes and telephones.  I just can
\rquote t be bothered with it these days.  Everything you do these days is rules or paperwork.  Sin
ce F&M the company has branched out into different things and they have grown from 45 wagons to nearly 80 and instead of one depot there is now five depots.  Although that doesn\rquote t affect me directly }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 has a lot more responsibility now and he is in meetings a lot more so I\rquote 
m left with it.  Since I said I was moving away I have been kept in the dark as to what is going on.  The other managers have been away on courses on management and man handling.  I don\rquote t find out unto after they have been.  I understand w
hy they are not sending me on these courses but I feel if they told  me it was happening I\rquote d feel better.  The way I feel at the moment I feel as if I\rquote m getting left behind and as if they are just using me until I go.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par I was out on a wagon today I was leading sheep into Longtown.  I enjoy it more on a wagon these days.  I\rquote m out of the way and can\rquote t see what is going on.  When I\rquote m in the office I feel like I\rquote 
m achieving something.  With the company growing as big it\rquote s not just a family firm anymore.  You can\rquote t get the same conversation out of the bosses as you used to. 
\par 
\par Weds
\par I was out on a wagon again this morning and I was supposed to go to Cockermouth this afternoon but sheep were too expensive so our customer didn\rquote t buy any.  There are still quite
 a few sheep about and a good demand for them so things are quite good just now.  Normally at this time of the year things are not so busy.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par There was quite a few Irish sheep in Longtown today.  Their retention period is off so a lot of the Irish 
farmers are off loading sheep when they are a good price.  The retention period is for the subsidies.  A farmer applies to the government for subsistence for keeping ewes and ewe lambs.  A farmer will apply for let\rquote 
s say 200 sheep and depending where he is it can vary  from \'a312 to \'a3
17 per female sheep.  So a lot of farmers keep hold of their old ewes ad the ewe lambs that are not really any good for breeding.  Some buy old ewes in just for their numbers.  When they apply for sub there is a period of time wh
en they have to keep that number of sheep.  In both GB and Ireland the forms have to be in by January and that number of sheep has to be kept.  Government officials can go to the farm and count at any time.  In GB this period of time (the retention period
)
 ends in the middle of May but in Ireland it ends in the middle of April.  This favours the Irish because British farmers are still keeping hold of their sheep and numbers in markets are less.  The Irish fetch their sheep over here and get good prices for
 them.
\par 
\par Friday
\par There wasn\rquote t a lot happening today with it being Good Friday and the Easter week-end.  Things weren\rquote t very busy.  I hope it stays that way because }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 is away this weekend.  His cousin is getting married on Monday in Ireland.  So I am on duty all weekend.  I took }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 to play with his cousins this morning.  Just out of Longtown both local farms had their dairy cows out on grass.  It was strange but really good to see it\rquote s the first time I\rquote ve seen cows in fields around Longtown for the last two year. 

\par 
\par Saturday
\par There was a meeting at work this morning about wages and holidays with the new working 
time directive coming in to place in August.  There was a lot of unhappy people came out of that meeting not because of the W.T.D. but about the way As were handling it and the way they were treating their workers.  Could be some fun this week or two.

\par 
\par Sunday
\par We took }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s Mam back to Kilmarnock today as she is going home tomorrow.  Grandpapa were chuffed to pieces to see }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
.  We spent most of the day at Kilmarnock and on the way home we met }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote s Mam and dropped him off because he is going hom
e as well.  It felt funny when we got home after being a busy house for a couple of weeks.  There was only me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 left.  I had to go into work when we got back to load some sheep so it was a late night.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s3\qj \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel2\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\fs24\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\insrsid13964281 Week 65
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\fs24\insrsid13964281 I don\rquote t really know why I bothered going into work today, there wasn\rquote 
t much happening anywhere.  I had one wagon cleared everything I had in Scotland today.  There was very little in markets anywhere today.
\par When I got home today }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was feeding }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  she noticed a littl
e rash behind her ear.  We phoned the Doctor and he asked us to take her round to see him.  He wasn\rquote t sure what it was so he asked us to take her to hospital.  They done tests to rule out all the serious viruses.  They couldn\rquote 
t tell us exactly what it was so they kept her in for the night.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  stayed as well because she was feeding }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  herself.  I couldn\rquote 
t stay because }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was away and I had the phones.
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par I was up at 07.30 this morning despite getting to bed at 02.30.  I phoned the hospital and they told me }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 had quite a good night.  The Doctor was coming round at 10.00 and he would decide whether they could come home or not.  I went to work and got sorted and men set off to different places.  I was trying to get someone t
o look after our office so I could go to the hospital.  Because only me and }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  know what is going on with the livestock there isn\rquote 
t really anybody who knows what is going on.  In the end at 11.00 I phoned }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and told him I was switching the phones through to him because I had t go.  When I got to the hospital }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 
[wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  had  had nothing to eat since 10 pm last night.  She was waiting to get a urine sample from }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 then we could go home.  I got her something to eat.  We got a sample about 1 pm.  I got }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 home and got them into the house then went back to work.  I only had to wait for }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  to get back home then I could go home.  }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 got home about 5 pm but disappeared.  I eventually phoned him at 7.30 pm so I could go home.  I wasn\rquote t very happy at all.
\par 
\par Weds
\par We had quite a good night considering the upheaval }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  had been through.  She was a lot better today settling down again.  The conclusion was that }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281  had a viral infection in her skin and just to keep an eye on her for the next
 48 hours.  I went to Cockermouth this afternoon.  I have never seen sheep as expensive as they were today.  Just before Xmas good hoggs were making ? per live kilo today average hoggs were making \'a3
1.70 per kilo.  There was a lot of smiling faces among the farmers.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par Things were busy this morning.  We took a lot of a sheep into Longtown.  With prices as good as they are and demand being so good there\rquote s quite a bit of stock about.  Sheep are getting less although there is quite a bit about there isn\rquote 
t quite as much as there was.  Where 2 to 3 month ago there might have been nearly 10 000 sheep on sale day but now there will only be 4 to 5 thousand.  Despite this there is still the same amount of buyers and the same demand that\rquote 
s why prices are so good.
\par 
\par Friday
\par Things are not  as busy today, it\rquote s nice to get a bit of time and get caught up.  I got the chance to have a good talk to }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  today.  I told }{\fs24\insrsid11086707 D}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 we would have to get somebody else trained to look after the office in case both of us are off work together.  I also told him that when I go he didn\rquote t have anybody else trained up, he would be left on his own.
\par 
\par Sat
\par Went shopping this afternoon apart from that done very little.
\par 
\par Sun
\par I didn\rquote t get up too early today.  By the time I made breakfast and got sorted it was nearly lunch time.  I took C}{\fs24\insrsid16677158  }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 to pick his rabbits up this afternoon.  When I got back I looked after }{
\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  so that }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  could go and get some sleep.  I was supposed to wake her up about 6pm but I prepared tea and fed }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281  so when I got }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  sorted I took her up to }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  at 8pm so I could cook tea.  We both just relaxed after tea.
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid1444251 
\par 
\par }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 Week 66
\par Back to the grind again just the usual Monday. The only difference today I took a load of sheep into Carlisle this morning.  There isn\rquote 
t as many sheep about today.  Although prices are good the numbers are less.  Most farmers now have sold last year\rquote s lambs are now busy lambing this year\rquote s lambs.  It\rquote 
s quite good because I am getting finished a bit earlier at night.  It\rquote s nice I get to spend more time with }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 .
\par 
\par Tuesday
\par Things were very quiet today.  \\I spent the afternoon spring cleaning my van.  It should have been done about Christmas time it was long overdue.  I washed it inside and out.  }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 \rquote 
s friend was in to see }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  when I got home from work.  }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was sleeping so she never got a cuddle tonight.
\par 
\par Weds
\par I started to spring clean the office today. For being a new office it\rquote s filthy.  I got my half of the office done or nearly all my half.  I went away f
or a load of peat this afternoon and then I went to Dumfries for a load of cattle.  We were talking today about the weather and I was saying it\rquote s funny I\rquote ve got strawberries flowering in my tub and normally they don\rquote 
t flower unto the end of May or June.  I just hope the weather dries up so the strawberries will ripen.
\par 
\par Thursday
\par We\rquote re not so busy today but Longtown is busy.  I didn\rquote t have to take any sheep in this morning because we had plenty of drivers about.  Today prices were very good.  This sort of trade couldn\rquote 
t last though it would be nice if it could but abattoirs can\rquote t stand paying these prices for too long.  The supermarkets are still paying the same price for the meat from abattoirs so abattoirs can\rquote 
t stand the difference in price for much longer.
\par 
\par Fri
\par I spent a lot of today with the company solicitor.  As I said a couple of weeks ago Defra are trying to claim money back off the company.  Now As are taking the case to them.  While talking to the solicitor I was surprised how things came flooding ba
ck to me.  There was a lot I had forgotten but it came back to me as I was talking to him.  He was telling me he is working full time on cases against Defra for incompetence.  I don\rquote 
t mind making a statement but at the same time it fetches memories I would rather forget.  Not all of it but some of it because It\rquote s something I will never forget.
\par 
\par Sat
\par }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  was away at he hairdresser today so me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  stayed at home and looked after }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
.  Mam and Dad were in this afternoon for an hour or so.  Maim hasn\rquote t been well.  She\rquote s had bronchitis and she has stopped smoking.  She is getting better now but she hasn\rquote t been very well.  They were at my cousin\rquote 
s wedding yesterday.  We would have liked to have gone but we didn\rquote t want to leave }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  with anybody else the way she has been lately.
\par 
\par Sunday
\par I had a bit of a lie in this morning.  After I got up I made breakfast then went and done a bit in the garage for a couple of hours.
\par I took }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  to her sister\rquote s this afternoon. Her and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [wife]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  are going to Islay for a couple of weeks.  I\rquote 
m working this next week and having the following week off and going to Islay.  We had our tea then me and }{\fs24\insrsid4859116 [son]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  came home.  It will be funny not having }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281  in the house again.  
\par 
\par 
\par }{\b\fs24\insrsid13964281 Week Number: }{\fs24\insrsid13964281 68
\par I was away at 2.30 a.m. this morning because I was catching the ferry at 7 a.m. }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [wife\rquote s sister]}{\fs24\insrsid13964281  came and picked me up at the ferry port and took me to the house. }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 [new baby]}{
\fs24\insrsid13964281  has changed quite a lot in a week, she\rquote s grown and filled out quite a lot. I was just nodding off this afternoon when }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 A}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 came in wanting a hand so I went away with him and ended up helping him all afternoon.
\par 
\par }\pard\plain \s1\qj \li0\ri0\keepn\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \b\f1\fs24\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\f0\insrsid13964281 Tuesday
\par }\pard\plain \qj \li0\ri0\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0 \fs20\lang2057\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp2057\langfenp1033 {\fs24\insrsid13964281 I went with }{\fs24\insrsid16677158 A}{\fs24\insrsid13964281 
 on his deliveries today. He has a big round now and he delivers eggs all over the island. We didn\rquote t get home until 7.
30 p.m. He was telling me that the new regulations coming in say that if you have more than 400 hens and you are supplying your eggs have to be stamped. He has to apply for a stamp number and the stamp machine will cost about \'a3
2500. He is not happy about it but he can\rquote 
t do anything about it. If he had less than 400 hens he could supply anywhere with eggs and need nothing. Just another example of governments idiotic rules. In this country nowadays you are not allowed to get on and do well for yourself unless
 you are breaking the law or have a lot of money to start with.
\par 
