sheep out there. I sent one lad to Penrith for a load of sheep to come to a farm in Penton. The first I knew I got a phone call from the farmer wanting to know why there was a wagon in his yard looking for a load of sheep to go to Penrith. Its no wonder I
 have to work to 11 p.m. at night. At least the farmer had seen the funny side of it!
